<subSubSection id="C311AFCBFF94BD42FF2EFE8289F8FE75" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB4FC40FF94BD42FF2EFE8289F8FE75" blockId="3.[178,1086,370,480]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">
Comment: This species was previously known only from the 
<typeStatus id="54B042E2FF94BD42FCE4FE838AA6FE1D" box="[888,932,371,392]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">type</typeStatus>
locality in the southwest of the Chinese province Yunnan (
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A81B1FF94BD42FDE7FE608A10FE33" author="ASSING V" box="[635,786,400,422]" journalOrPublisher="Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552" pagination="89 - 148" part="61" refId="ref3466" refString="ASSING V. (2011 a): A revision of the genus Neosclerus CAMERON (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern 61 (1): 89 - 148." title="A revision of the genus Neosclerus CAMERON (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae)" type="journal article" year="2011">ASSING 2011a</bibRefCitation>
). The aedeagus of one of the males from 
<collectingCountry id="F31CBCD0FF94BD42FEB0FE5E885FFE56" box="[300,349,430,451]" name="Laos" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">Laos</collectingCountry>
is illustrated in 
<figureCitation id="1330E0C5FF94BD42FD9FFE5D8B43FE56" box="[515,577,429,451]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="4.[178,218,1229,1249]" captionTargetBox="[179,1085,212,1212]" captionTargetId="figure-201@4.[178,1085,212,1218]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-8: Neosclerus macer nov.sp. (1-7) and N. schuelkei ASSING (8): (1) forebody; (2) male sternite VII; (3) male sternite VIII in ventral view; (4) anterior carinae of male sternite VIII in ventral view; (5) male sternite VIII in lateral view; (6, 8) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 0.5 mm; 2-3, 5: 0.2 mm; 4, 6-8: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302506/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
. The currently known distribution is illustrated in 
<figureCitation id="1330E0C5FF94BD42FF2EFE3B89F4FE75" box="[178,246,458,480]" captionStart="Map 2" captionStartId="2.[178,223,1513,1533]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,529,1498]" captionTargetId="figure-134@2.[178,1085,529,1498]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Map 2: Distributions of Neosclerus praeacutus ASSING (filled triangles: male-based records; open triangles: female-based records) and N. schuelkei ASSING (circles) in South Asia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302504" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302504/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">Map 2</figureCitation>
